         <div type="translation">
            <ab>
               <supplied reason="lost">So-and-so honoured</supplied> Publius Aelius Septimius Mannus, the <term xml:lang="la">clarissimus</term>, governor (<term xml:lang="la">praeses</term>), consular, distinguished, brave, pure, generous, having achieved all virtue, his/its benefactor <gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/>
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The honouring body was a single masculine entity; while this could have been a grateful individual, it is perhaps more likely that such an important text was put up by the demos.</p>
            <p>See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="I.15" target=".xml"/>.</p>
